WestLangley\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"WestLangley","type":"User","id":1000017,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/orgs"}},{"index":9,"author_association":"NONE","body":"I seem to not be able to merge larger geometries. WebGL throws buffer-overflow errors. It works for smaller geometries. I found conflicting information regarding this - at one place saying webGL is limited to UInt6 and 65535 vertices, but then there's OES_element_index_uint which should in theory allow UInt32 and bump vertices up to 4294967296. My browser supports that for sure. In any case, documents also mix indicies and vertices so i'm not sure what exactly is limited.\n\nIs there a definitive answer for this?  Has anyone tried merging large BufferGeometries with this?\n","created_at":"2016-03-12T12:21:15.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/pull\/8162#issuecomment-195728738","id":195728738,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/8162","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDE5NTcyODczOA==","updated_at":"2016-03-12T12:21:15.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/195728738","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/drcmda\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/drcmda\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars0.githubusercontent.com\/u\/2223602?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/drcmda","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/drcmda\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/drcmda","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/drcmda\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjIyMjM2MDI=","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/